1
00:01:06,336 --> 00:01:10,778
=The Truth=

2
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,136
=Episode 17=

3
00:01:14,520 --> 00:01:16,800
You actually underestimated us.

4
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:21,041
Something like this is nothing for us.

5
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:24,240
You think you could hide it?

6
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:27,681
Be honest.

7
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:30,240
You two were so close.

8
00:01:30,761 --> 00:01:32,520
You must know what happened to him.

9
00:01:33,960 --> 00:01:35,960
What happened?

10
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:39,440
Liao Guangyong is dead.

11
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,041
What? He's dead?

12
00:01:42,041 --> 00:01:44,041
H-How did he die?

13
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:46,440
Based on the evidence we have,

14
00:01:47,481 --> 00:01:51,641
this woman might be the murderer.

15
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:53,201
She killed Mr. Liao?

16
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:56,041
Mr. Liao lent you his car.

17
00:01:56,561 --> 00:02:00,160
So you might have a motive
to kill him too.

18
00:02:00,481 --> 00:02:02,001
Th-This has nothing to do with me!

19
00:02:02,001 --> 00:02:03,641
Y-You should go arrest this woman!

20
00:02:04,761 --> 00:02:06,481
B-But due to insufficient evidence,

21
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:07,720
we can't arrest her.

22
00:02:08,040 --> 00:02:08,600
Officer,

23
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,200
p-protect me!

24
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:10,160
Sit down and talk.

25
00:02:10,361 --> 00:02:10,880
Okay.

26
00:02:12,841 --> 00:02:13,760
Actually,

27
00:02:13,841 --> 00:02:17,440
I had nothing to do with that car crash.

28
00:02:19,081 --> 00:02:19,880
I...

29
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:22,440
It was Mr. Liao.

30
00:02:22,801 --> 00:02:23,600
He drank.

31
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,040
H-He was driving the car.

32
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:27,401
I was sitting in the back seat.

33
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:29,600
After hitting a person, he ran off.

34
00:02:30,001 --> 00:02:31,440
He left me alone in the car.

35
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,440
He wanted me to take the fall.

36
00:02:34,281 --> 00:02:37,561
I got my license five or six years ago,

37
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:39,961
but I've never driven since.

38
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,600
How could I possibly drive
and hit someone?

39
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:44,401
I...

40
00:02:46,841 --> 00:02:49,361
I was short on money at that time.

41
00:02:50,521 --> 00:02:51,801
My mom was sick.

42
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:53,760
My kid needed school fees.

43
00:02:55,121 --> 00:02:58,401
So, I...

44
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:02,760
No rush.

45
00:03:03,361 --> 00:03:04,241
Take your time.

46
00:03:26,961 --> 00:03:27,801
Dad.

47
00:03:30,081 --> 00:03:30,880
Dad.

48
00:03:56,281 --> 00:03:58,640
Looks like he might have bone damage.

49
00:03:58,760 --> 00:03:59,920
The bruising is severe too.

50
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:01,208
Need to reduce inflammation.

51
00:04:01,961 --> 00:04:03,001
I saw his medical history.

52
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,241
He has a history of Alzheimer's?

53
00:04:05,241 --> 00:04:05,920
Yes.

54
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,801
Let's observe him for a few hours first.

55
00:04:10,136 --> 00:04:11,920
Once the outpatient service opens
tomorrow,

56
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:12,880
go get a CT scan.

57
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:13,480
Got it.

58
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:13,961
That's all.

59
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:15,001
Thanks.

60
00:04:21,121 --> 00:04:21,801
Hello?

61
00:04:21,801 --> 00:04:22,481
Captain Leng.

62
00:04:22,681 --> 00:04:23,960
Jiao, what's up?

63
00:04:24,241 --> 00:04:27,200
We might have found the connection
between Zhao Junxin and Jiang Yuzhen.

64
00:04:28,161 --> 00:04:30,161
Young people have agile minds.

65
00:04:30,161 --> 00:04:31,801
I only focused on checking surveillance,

66
00:04:31,801 --> 00:04:33,481
but Long came up with a good idea.

67
00:04:33,481 --> 00:04:34,361
Long, you explain.

68
00:04:34,921 --> 00:04:36,200
Captain Leng, here's the thing.

69
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:38,440
Most payments are now made online,

70
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:39,640
with payment notifications.

71
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:41,400
If she used a card,
there'd be a text alert.

72
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:42,121
So,

73
00:04:42,121 --> 00:04:45,640
I looked for relevant pushes and texts
they received in the last six months.

74
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:46,880
And I actually found something.

75
00:04:47,241 --> 00:04:50,601
Zhao Junxin and Jiang Yuzhen once went
to a children's playground

76
00:04:50,601 --> 00:04:52,760
at the same time, on the same day,

77
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:53,840
literally minutes apart.

78
00:04:54,561 --> 00:04:56,481
Playground? Where is it?

79
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,320
This guy sure has an appetite.

80
00:05:39,561 --> 00:05:42,001
He is already stuffed
but still has room for bubble tea.

81
00:05:42,721 --> 00:05:44,681
But he really knows
how to keep his cool.

82
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:46,320
After gaining so much dirty money,

83
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:49,280
I thought he'd be splurging
and showing off like crazy.

84
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,080
Of course, he wants to show off.

85
00:05:52,721 --> 00:05:53,721
He hasn't had the money,

86
00:05:53,721 --> 00:05:55,681
but he's already started
looking at new big houses

87
00:05:55,681 --> 00:05:57,681
that he actually can't afford.

88
00:05:58,280 --> 00:05:59,601
Is he truly keeping his cool?

89
00:06:00,721 --> 00:06:01,880
The insurance company refuses

90
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:04,960
to pay out now
by citing the ongoing investigation,

91
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:07,200
and he can't sell the watches
or jewelry,

92
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:08,760
or he would start to spend.

93
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:49,801
I don't need a cab. Just go.

94
00:07:26,161 --> 00:07:28,361
Ye, I've hit another dead end.

95
00:07:28,361 --> 00:07:30,280
Where do you think he hid the stuff?

96
00:07:30,361 --> 00:07:31,601
We've gone through his place,

97
00:07:31,601 --> 00:07:32,561
yet found nothing.

98
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:35,280
No entries in his
or Jiang Yuzhen's accounts either.

99
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:38,561
After the crime,

100
00:07:39,561 --> 00:07:42,161
he's stayed
within a 5-kilometer radius of his home.

101
00:07:42,481 --> 00:07:43,960
He hasn't gone any further.

102
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:46,520
The stolen goods should be
within this area.

103
00:07:47,361 --> 00:07:48,760
But this area is way too big.

104
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:50,361
We can't possibly search everywhere.

105
00:07:57,161 --> 00:07:58,280
Just follow him.

106
00:08:50,121 --> 00:08:51,121
So?

107
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:53,361
So you lied.

108
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:56,321
The surveillance video shows it clearly.

109
00:08:57,201 --> 00:08:59,361
You spoke with Jiang Yuzhen.

110
00:09:00,001 --> 00:09:01,760
And it wasn't a short conversation.

111
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:06,361
Do you know what we talked about?

112
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:08,361
Aren't you worried at all?

113
00:09:11,441 --> 00:09:13,160
What do I have to worry about?

114
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,121
I committed a crime.

115
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:21,361
I killed Jiang Yuzhen
and Liao Guangyong,

116
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,321
including his mistress

117
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:26,160
and the child in her belly.

118
00:09:26,481 --> 00:09:27,961
Put it all on me.

119
00:09:29,841 --> 00:09:31,160
I killed them all.

120
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,001
My child died.

121
00:09:38,361 --> 00:09:39,201
They

122
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:43,601
won't get away alive.

123
00:09:45,481 --> 00:09:46,280
Zhao Junxin.

124
00:09:47,081 --> 00:09:48,560
The country has laws.

125
00:09:49,241 --> 00:09:51,961
If you insist on this,
none of us can help you.

126
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:53,800
Anything else you want to ask?

127
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:56,081
If not, I'm going back.

128
00:10:00,361 --> 00:10:02,001
(So are you really at ease now?)

129
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:05,520
(Does it still hurt
when you think of your child?)

130
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:08,241
(I haven't dreamed of my child
in a long time.)

131
00:10:09,721 --> 00:10:15,361
(Maybe he blames me for killing
and doesn't want to see me.)

132
00:10:17,280 --> 00:10:19,241
(Because you're not a loony.)

133
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,800
(It's not that you're unafraid.)

134
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:24,560
(You can only lie to yourself
that you did this for your child.)

135
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:27,721
(Will doing this bring your child back?)

136
00:10:38,121 --> 00:10:39,441
If nothing unexpected happens,

137
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,601
this is our second-to-last time meeting.

138
00:10:44,121 --> 00:10:45,241
Next time...

139
00:10:45,361 --> 00:10:46,081
Zhao Junxin,

140
00:10:46,961 --> 00:10:48,280
you'll keep your word, right?

141
00:10:49,201 --> 00:10:51,481
Don't let me finish the job
and then you...

142
00:10:53,081 --> 00:10:55,001
You don't need to doubt me.

143
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:56,880
To be honest,

144
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,280
I wish I were you

145
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:01,321
so that I could personally have revenge.

146
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:05,880
Poisoning him is too good for him.

147
00:11:08,481 --> 00:11:10,481
You wouldn't want to live my life.

148
00:11:13,081 --> 00:11:14,680
I'm already like this anyway.

149
00:11:15,601 --> 00:11:16,680
I'll just take the gamble.

150
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,441
I trust you.

151
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,880
Let's stick to what we agreed before.

152
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:29,601
Wait for my message.

153
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:31,520
Don't worry.

154
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:56,481
(No. My child won't come back.)

155
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:59,481
(So stop lying to yourself.)

156
00:14:00,081 --> 00:14:03,121
(Think carefully
about what's right and what's wrong.)

157
00:14:03,721 --> 00:14:06,040
(Revenge isn't a free pass
for "lynching".)

158
00:14:06,441 --> 00:14:08,560
(The law is the measure of justice.)

159
00:14:29,601 --> 00:14:31,081
(CT Interventional Suite)
Family of Leng Xingguo?

160
00:14:33,624 --> 00:14:34,841
The wound has been treated.

161
00:14:34,841 --> 00:14:35,680
Nothing serious.

162
00:14:35,768 --> 00:14:36,481
Here's his bill.

163
00:14:36,481 --> 00:14:37,920
Go pay over there.

164
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:43,721
Liu Yang.

165
00:14:44,081 --> 00:14:46,121
Did you know
Captain Leng's dad was hospitalized?

166
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:48,081
I heard the hired nurse wasn't reliable.

167
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:49,680
She got off work early.

168
00:14:50,081 --> 00:14:52,241
So, his dad fell at home.

169
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:54,800
Should we go visit him?

170
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:56,121
Forget it.

171
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:58,481
I don't think
Captain Leng wants us to go.

172
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:01,520
If you make a big deal about it,
Captain Leng won't be happy.

173
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:02,400
Also,

174
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:04,841
be careful of buttering him up
in the wrong way.

175
00:15:23,256 --> 00:15:27,662
(No-Name Diner)

176
00:15:27,721 --> 00:15:29,081
The soup I made for you is ready.

177
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:32,400
Just a moment.

178
00:15:36,361 --> 00:15:37,800
Stop working.

179
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:39,280
You have the soup.

180
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:41,560
Just leave the rest of the work to me.

181
00:15:42,321 --> 00:15:44,520
No, you get muddled
when you do the accounts.

182
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:45,441
I'll do it myself.

183
00:15:45,441 --> 00:15:46,520
It'll be done soon.

184
00:15:48,081 --> 00:15:50,601
Look, you haven't slept well lately.

185
00:15:50,721 --> 00:15:53,680
Have some soup to nourish yourself,
and it'll help you sleep better.

186
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:55,520
Please.

187
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:56,880
It's almost done, you...

188
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:58,121
Having the soup matters now.

189
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:01,841
That's so much.

190
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:05,680
Let me do this.

191
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,481
It's been incredibly busy.

192
00:16:07,481 --> 00:16:08,680
Qiming hasn't come by either.

193
00:16:08,961 --> 00:16:11,040
I haven't even had time
to ask about his dad.

194
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:14,961
When the hired nurse left early,

195
00:16:14,961 --> 00:16:16,520
his dad took a fall.

196
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:19,680
Qiming's been worried sick over it.

197
00:16:20,481 --> 00:16:22,121
At that age, a fall is serious.

198
00:16:22,121 --> 00:16:22,800
Yeah.

199
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:24,321
What's wrong with that nurse?

200
00:16:24,321 --> 00:16:25,441
She is irresponsible.

201
00:16:26,481 --> 00:16:28,880
I'll make some good food tomorrow
for his dad.

202
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:31,160
Alas.

203
00:16:32,201 --> 00:16:33,001
Delicious.

204
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:35,560
When we get old,

205
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:37,241
it's tough not having our son around.

206
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:44,081
I've already thought it through.

207
00:16:44,481 --> 00:16:45,880
After I retire,

208
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:48,721
we'll find a nice nursing home.

209
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:52,201
We can cook every day, watch the sea,

210
00:16:52,481 --> 00:16:54,040
and take good care of ourselves.

211
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:56,040
Just live our lives well.

212
00:16:56,760 --> 00:16:57,560
Jiao.

213
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:00,081
I dreamed about our son the other day.

214
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:04,241
He said a lot to me.

215
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:07,681
He told us to take care of ourselves.

216
00:17:08,681 --> 00:17:10,001
If we live well,

217
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,881
he will rest in peace.

218
00:17:16,921 --> 00:17:17,721
Indeed,

219
00:17:18,080 --> 00:17:19,520
we need to take care of ourselves

220
00:17:19,881 --> 00:17:21,201
and live well.

221
00:17:21,681 --> 00:17:23,320
Setting our son at ease matters most.

222
00:18:32,001 --> 00:18:33,441
Hello? Ziwu.

223
00:18:34,161 --> 00:18:35,001
What's up?

224
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,441
Nothing.

225
00:18:37,881 --> 00:18:39,721
I didn't call about work.

226
00:18:41,481 --> 00:18:42,201
Go ahead.

227
00:18:44,881 --> 00:18:46,040
How's your dad?

228
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:47,280
Is he okay?

229
00:18:47,921 --> 00:18:49,001
He's fine.

230
00:18:49,481 --> 00:18:50,481
He is already asleep.

231
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:55,921
You should rest early
if there is nothing else.

232
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:00,881
Oh, Ziwu.

233
00:19:01,681 --> 00:19:06,481
Please clean up the crime scene reports

234
00:19:06,921 --> 00:19:09,320
on the Fuquan Community

235
00:19:09,921 --> 00:19:12,001
and the Central Hospital.

236
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:13,721
Make sure nothing's missed.

237
00:19:15,201 --> 00:19:17,280
Okay. Good night.

238
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:26,520
Hello? Mr. Li.

239
00:19:27,681 --> 00:19:28,320
Enough.

240
00:19:28,320 --> 00:19:30,800
Stop apologizing.

241
00:19:31,481 --> 00:19:33,481
I don't have time
to claim compensation from you.

242
00:19:34,001 --> 00:19:35,721
Just hurry up

243
00:19:35,721 --> 00:19:37,600
and find me a reliable nurse quickly.

244
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:39,560
The sooner, the better. Okay?

245
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:41,520
Thank you.

246
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:42,681
Good. Okay.

247
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:57,161
(Ziwu.)

248
00:19:58,881 --> 00:20:00,520
(Did the tests show any leads?)

249
00:20:01,520 --> 00:20:02,681
Yes.

250
00:20:03,721 --> 00:20:04,401
Let's hear it.

251
00:20:13,441 --> 00:20:15,641
Wait, just a sec.

252
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:20,401
Well, at the crime scene,

253
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:25,360
from the blood droplets near the victim,

254
00:20:25,360 --> 00:20:27,040
I extracted two sets of DNA.

255
00:20:27,201 --> 00:20:30,481
The first set
belongs to the victim himself.

256
00:20:31,161 --> 00:20:33,600
I checked. It's not from his relatives.

257
00:20:33,721 --> 00:20:36,280
The other set is unknown.

258
00:20:37,001 --> 00:20:38,001
Not exactly unknown,

259
00:20:38,001 --> 00:20:42,681
it's just an unidentified DNA profile.

260
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:46,320
It could have been left by the suspect.

261
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:49,800
DNA tests gave us a direction.

262
00:20:50,441 --> 00:20:51,080
Right.

263
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:46,881
It's so late.

264
00:21:47,721 --> 00:21:48,721
You're still working?

265
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:50,721
Sorry, Captain Leng.

266
00:21:50,840 --> 00:21:52,120
I disturbed your rest.

267
00:21:52,441 --> 00:21:55,320
I saw the light on here from my office.

268
00:21:55,320 --> 00:21:56,520
So I wanted to turn it off.

269
00:21:56,721 --> 00:21:57,800
Then I saw you sleeping.

270
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,921
I thought the light might bother you.

271
00:21:59,921 --> 00:22:02,040
So I went to turn it off,
but then you woke up.

272
00:22:03,921 --> 00:22:05,040
Head home early.

273
00:22:05,921 --> 00:22:06,881
Write reports tomorrow.

274
00:22:08,001 --> 00:22:08,961
I'll walk you back.

275
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:09,921
No need, Captain Leng.

276
00:22:09,921 --> 00:22:12,472
I live very close.

277
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:14,320
I live there too. It's on my way.

278
00:22:15,201 --> 00:22:16,441
Go pack up your stuff.

279
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:19,320
Yes.

280
00:22:27,481 --> 00:22:28,040
Captain Leng.

281
00:22:35,001 --> 00:22:35,721
Captain Leng.

282
00:22:35,721 --> 00:22:36,441
Going to lunch?

283
00:22:36,681 --> 00:22:37,320
Okay.

284
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:44,481
Is this all you're having for lunch?

285
00:22:46,744 --> 00:22:48,040
I just grabbed something quick.

286
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:48,921
I'm not very hungry.

287
00:22:50,961 --> 00:22:52,600
I got you a sandwich.

288
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:54,161
For me?

289
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:56,161
Thank you.

290
00:22:56,161 --> 00:22:58,921
And some tomatoes.

291
00:22:59,161 --> 00:23:00,161
Captain Leng, I...

292
00:23:02,161 --> 00:23:03,560
Do you already have the results?

293
00:23:05,241 --> 00:23:06,520
Let me do a final check.

294
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:07,280
I'll print it out

295
00:23:07,280 --> 00:23:08,441
and bring it to you.

296
00:23:08,441 --> 00:23:09,120
Okay.

297
00:23:09,441 --> 00:23:10,201
Eat.

298
00:23:13,641 --> 00:23:14,800
No need, I...

299
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:18,001
It's sweet.

300
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:19,961
You like tomatoes?

301
00:23:20,441 --> 00:23:21,721
Yes, to get vitamins.

302
00:23:22,360 --> 00:23:23,360
Finish your lunch.

303
00:23:51,481 --> 00:23:52,360
Morning, Ziwu.

304
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:39,384
(Yongguang Supermarket)

305
00:24:59,721 --> 00:25:00,320
Qian.

306
00:25:00,881 --> 00:25:02,161
The suspect entered the mall,

307
00:25:02,320 --> 00:25:03,384
going to the second floor.

308
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:04,921
Still on him?

309
00:25:05,201 --> 00:25:06,280
Not many people inside.

310
00:25:06,520 --> 00:25:07,360
Can't get too close.

311
00:25:09,080 --> 00:25:09,800
Got it.

312
00:25:10,201 --> 00:25:11,161
Keep your distance.

313
00:26:09,080 --> 00:26:10,280
Did he go to the lockers?

314
00:26:13,241 --> 00:26:13,881
Yes.

315
00:26:14,401 --> 00:26:15,481
Leaving already?

316
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:19,481
He went into a store,

317
00:26:19,481 --> 00:26:20,481
ordered, and took a seat.

318
00:26:22,560 --> 00:26:23,201
Okay.

319
00:26:24,120 --> 00:26:25,320
Probably it'll take a while.

320
00:26:25,840 --> 00:26:28,201
He'll head straight
to the bus stop when he leaves.

321
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:29,961
Keep tailing him.

322
00:26:30,641 --> 00:26:31,600
I'll loop around.

323
00:26:31,600 --> 00:26:32,800
Meet you at the bus stop.

324
00:26:57,401 --> 00:27:02,320
Would he really hide stolen goods
in a place like this?

325
00:27:05,481 --> 00:27:08,040
These self-service lockers
are the least conspicuous.

326
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:10,201
Usually, no one pays them any mind.

327
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:11,681
After the crime,

328
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:14,120
Geng Tianchou visited this supermarket
every day,

329
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:14,921
yet never shopped.

330
00:27:14,921 --> 00:27:16,360
He just wandered around and left.

331
00:27:16,520 --> 00:27:18,360
He's not the homemaker type.

332
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:20,961
So he went there for the lockers.

333
00:27:22,120 --> 00:27:24,161
But shouldn't this place have cameras?

334
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:25,760
Yes.

335
00:27:26,001 --> 00:27:27,080
But due to camera angles,

336
00:27:27,921 --> 00:27:30,280
only the two rows
he approached are covered.

337
00:27:31,441 --> 00:27:33,681
We haven't confirmed
the exact right locker.

338
00:27:34,681 --> 00:27:35,560
Quite certain?

339
00:27:35,681 --> 00:27:36,280
Yes.

340
00:27:36,881 --> 00:27:39,001
But ideally, we catch him red-handed.

341
00:27:39,921 --> 00:27:43,840
We have evidence against Jiang Yuzhen
and Zhao Junxin individually.

342
00:27:44,481 --> 00:27:47,080
Yet proving collusion is trickier.

343
00:27:48,040 --> 00:27:49,840
Zhao Junxin remains silent.

344
00:27:50,401 --> 00:27:53,881
Geng Tianchou is more likely to slip up.

345
00:27:56,080 --> 00:27:57,280
Three's enough.

346
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:00,481
Save some.

347
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:01,681
It's pretty sweet.

348
00:28:01,681 --> 00:28:02,241
Alright.

349
00:28:18,441 --> 00:28:19,641
Come on.

350
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:27,080
Who is it? Give me a break!

351
00:28:27,320 --> 00:28:28,401
This is CID.

352
00:28:29,001 --> 00:28:31,161
We found a bag
and phone likely belonging

353
00:28:31,441 --> 00:28:32,600
to your mother, Jiang Yuzhen.

354
00:28:32,881 --> 00:28:34,280
Come identify them.

355
00:28:35,641 --> 00:28:36,600
Impossible.

356
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:39,040
When?

357
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:40,961
I'm about to get off work.

358
00:28:41,481 --> 00:28:42,201
Come tomorrow.

359
00:28:42,201 --> 00:28:44,040
Wait, what did you say?

360
00:28:44,040 --> 00:28:44,800
Hello?

361
00:29:17,881 --> 00:29:19,520
Locker 12.

362
00:29:19,520 --> 00:29:20,641
Door open.

363
00:29:20,641 --> 00:29:22,401
Close the door
after retrieving your items.

364
00:29:22,961 --> 00:29:24,441
Locker 01.

365
00:29:24,441 --> 00:29:25,560
Door open.

366
00:29:25,560 --> 00:29:27,401
Close the door
after retrieving your items.

367
00:29:27,608 --> 00:29:28,628
Gosh!

368
00:29:29,001 --> 00:29:30,080
I'm quite scared.

369
00:29:55,840 --> 00:29:56,961
I've told you many times.

370
00:29:56,961 --> 00:29:58,881
I really don't know
where the stuff came from.

371
00:29:58,881 --> 00:30:00,560
My mom gave it to me
before she left home.

372
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:01,881
She told me to hide it well.

373
00:30:02,520 --> 00:30:03,681
Your mom told you to hide it?

374
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:05,641
Did you know what was inside?

375
00:30:05,641 --> 00:30:06,520
No, I don't.

376
00:30:06,961 --> 00:30:07,760
Really?

377
00:30:08,241 --> 00:30:09,520
Then why go to the sales office

378
00:30:09,520 --> 00:30:10,401
and the bank?

379
00:30:10,681 --> 00:30:11,401
Why?

380
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:13,080
I was just hanging out.

381
00:30:13,080 --> 00:30:14,201
What's wrong with that?

382
00:30:14,721 --> 00:30:15,520
Look where you are.

383
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:16,641
Watch your attitude.

384
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:20,881
Weren't you even a little curious?

385
00:30:22,080 --> 00:30:23,241
My mom told me to.

386
00:30:23,241 --> 00:30:24,800
She wouldn't hurt me.

387
00:30:25,481 --> 00:30:27,241
Did you find the locker yourself?

388
00:30:27,641 --> 00:30:29,280
No, my mom did it.

389
00:30:29,441 --> 00:30:31,001
I truly know nothing.

390
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,641
Last time, when we asked
about the bag and phone,

391
00:30:33,921 --> 00:30:34,881
why did you lie?

392
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:36,881
My mom told me to hide them.

393
00:30:36,881 --> 00:30:38,080
So I listened to her.

394
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:40,881
You're a grown adult.

395
00:30:41,001 --> 00:30:42,600
You just blindly do whatever she says?

396
00:30:42,721 --> 00:30:44,040
Even if it's illegal?

397
00:30:44,040 --> 00:30:45,760
I didn't know it was illegal!

398
00:30:46,681 --> 00:30:47,800
You didn't know?

399
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:50,481
Let me tell you now.

400
00:30:51,441 --> 00:30:55,681
Current evidence strongly suggests
your mother murdered and stole.

401
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:59,881
And you're covering up her crimes.

402
00:31:01,241 --> 00:31:02,161
What?

403
00:31:03,520 --> 00:31:05,560
But I really didn't know anything!

404
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:08,080
He is heartless.

405
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:12,120
He pinned all the bad stuff on his mom.

406
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:15,040
Then tell us

407
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:18,241
what Jiang Yuzhen did
on the day of the crime.

408
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:20,520
Again?

409
00:31:20,520 --> 00:31:21,881
I've said it so many times.

410
00:31:23,080 --> 00:31:23,881
Fine.

411
00:31:25,120 --> 00:31:27,481
My mom came back
from the Fuquan Community that day.

412
00:31:27,481 --> 00:31:29,401
Didn't you guys drop her off
at the gate?

413
00:31:29,921 --> 00:31:31,120
The next day, she went

414
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:32,280
to the hospital to see Liao.

415
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:34,040
And then she...

416
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:36,040
Did Jiang Yuzhen go out in between?

417
00:31:37,080 --> 00:31:38,481
Probably not.

418
00:31:38,481 --> 00:31:39,921
She just did what she used to do.

419
00:31:39,921 --> 00:31:40,881
She cooked for me

420
00:31:40,881 --> 00:31:42,681
and sorted through her junk.

421
00:31:43,280 --> 00:31:44,888
When did she give you the stolen goods?

422
00:31:45,881 --> 00:31:47,961
Before she went to the hospital.

423
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:49,800
What exactly did she say?

424
00:31:50,401 --> 00:31:51,641
She didn't say much.

425
00:31:51,641 --> 00:31:53,120
She just told me to hide the stuff

426
00:31:53,120 --> 00:31:54,392
and not to let anyone find it.

427
00:31:55,080 --> 00:31:55,921
Think again.

428
00:31:56,241 --> 00:31:57,401
The day before the crime,

429
00:31:57,961 --> 00:31:59,881
did Jiang Yuzhen do anything unusual?

430
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:03,760
I really don't know.

431
00:32:03,760 --> 00:32:04,681
I didn't notice.

432
00:32:05,241 --> 00:32:07,520
When did you find the insurance?

433
00:32:10,280 --> 00:32:12,201
I found it after the incident.

434
00:32:12,201 --> 00:32:14,840
It was right under her pillow.

435
00:32:17,481 --> 00:32:19,560
How did you find out
Jiang Yuzhen was in trouble?

436
00:32:21,241 --> 00:32:24,001
Someone told me.

437
00:32:24,001 --> 00:32:24,921
Who told you?

438
00:32:29,241 --> 00:32:30,401
Liao's wife.

439
00:32:32,481 --> 00:32:33,641
You know Miao Xiaolan?

440
00:32:35,441 --> 00:32:36,401
How do you know her?

441
00:32:38,401 --> 00:32:40,600
My mom worked for them for years.

442
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:42,921
When I was little,
my mom took me to their home for meals.

443
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:45,641
Back then, Liao wasn't a big shot yet.

444
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:49,481
When exactly did she
send you the message?

445
00:32:49,681 --> 00:32:50,760
What exactly did it say?

446
00:32:51,520 --> 00:32:53,040
It was that afternoon.

447
00:32:53,040 --> 00:32:54,641
I don't remember the exact time.

448
00:32:54,641 --> 00:32:56,280
She suddenly sent me a text,

449
00:32:56,280 --> 00:32:57,441
saying my mom was in trouble

450
00:32:57,441 --> 00:32:58,441
and at Central Hospital.

451
00:32:59,080 --> 00:32:59,800
Anything else?

452
00:33:07,241 --> 00:33:08,481
Do you know Miao Xiaolan well?

453
00:33:09,401 --> 00:33:11,080
Not really, but my mom does.

454
00:33:11,080 --> 00:33:12,481
They were old neighbors, after all.

455
00:33:12,961 --> 00:33:13,961
Old neighbors?

456
00:33:15,040 --> 00:33:16,161
Didn't you know?

457
00:33:16,600 --> 00:33:18,001
They were neighbors

458
00:33:18,001 --> 00:33:20,120
and classmates at primary school.

459
00:33:57,848 --> 00:34:03,768
(Tomatoes are delicious.)

460
00:34:32,952 --> 00:34:37,432
(Longyan)

461
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:39,481
Is your boss in?

462
00:34:39,481 --> 00:34:40,441
My boss is inside.

463
00:34:41,321 --> 00:34:42,441
Okay. Thanks.

464
00:35:00,680 --> 00:35:01,640
Want something to eat?

465
00:35:04,321 --> 00:35:05,160
No money on me.

466
00:35:06,881 --> 00:35:07,881
My treat.

467
00:35:07,881 --> 00:35:08,720
I told you.

468
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:11,281
I'm not here to eat.

469
00:35:13,801 --> 00:35:14,761
So?

470
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:19,080
I came to see you.

471
00:35:20,881 --> 00:35:22,281
You don't have to.

472
00:35:22,281 --> 00:35:23,281
Same as usual.

473
00:35:26,001 --> 00:35:27,401
I've been working in the kitchen.

474
00:35:27,401 --> 00:35:28,921
I even learned how to cook salmon.

475
00:35:31,120 --> 00:35:32,520
That doesn't sound like you.

476
00:35:33,441 --> 00:35:35,080
Well, I'm free now.

477
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:36,921
I might as well learn a skill.

478
00:35:37,921 --> 00:35:39,801
If this store ever shuts down,

479
00:35:39,801 --> 00:35:40,640
and I'm broke,

480
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:41,881
I can be a chef.

481
00:35:43,441 --> 00:35:44,401
Count me in.

482
00:35:44,881 --> 00:35:46,080
I'm half a chef myself.

483
00:35:47,801 --> 00:35:49,160
I haven't forgiven you, you know.

484
00:35:49,680 --> 00:35:53,160
Si Yuanlong gave me a game console.
I cut you into pieces on it every day.

485
00:35:55,240 --> 00:35:56,040
Fair enough.

486
00:36:19,001 --> 00:36:19,720
I'm fine.

487
00:36:20,881 --> 00:36:21,560
Don't worry.

488
00:36:32,481 --> 00:36:33,281
I'm sorry.

489
00:36:35,881 --> 00:36:38,080
We've known each other
since kindergarten.

490
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:40,281
No need to apologize.

491
00:36:41,881 --> 00:36:42,680
I know.

492
00:36:43,520 --> 00:36:44,761
Love fades away,

493
00:36:46,441 --> 00:36:47,600
yet friendship will remain.

494
00:36:54,841 --> 00:36:56,080
Alright, I've got work to do.

495
00:36:56,321 --> 00:36:57,441
Help yourself.

496
00:37:17,481 --> 00:37:19,001
It's pretty busy today.

497
00:37:19,361 --> 00:37:20,600
Sorry to keep you waiting.

498
00:37:21,361 --> 00:37:22,160
Thanks.

499
00:37:22,160 --> 00:37:22,881
Not at all.

500
00:37:23,481 --> 00:37:24,240
Lei.

501
00:37:26,680 --> 00:37:27,321
Lei.

502
00:37:27,481 --> 00:37:28,281
Captain Hao.

503
00:37:28,321 --> 00:37:28,801
Come on in.

504
00:37:28,801 --> 00:37:30,160
There are seats here. Over here.

505
00:37:30,160 --> 00:37:30,600
Okay.

506
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:31,481
- Over here.
- Okay.

507
00:37:31,481 --> 00:37:33,001
I haven't seen you lately.

508
00:37:33,001 --> 00:37:34,200
What case are you working on?

509
00:37:35,200 --> 00:37:35,640
Sit.

510
00:37:35,640 --> 00:37:37,080
Still on the fraud case.

511
00:37:37,481 --> 00:37:38,560
- Hi.
- It's been almost a year.

512
00:37:38,881 --> 00:37:40,080
It's finally wrapping up.

513
00:37:40,080 --> 00:37:41,640
Look, I've worked my hair right off.

514
00:37:43,481 --> 00:37:44,841
Come on, you were already bald.

515
00:37:45,520 --> 00:37:46,600
- Come on.
- Sit.

516
00:37:46,600 --> 00:37:48,520
Come on, sit down.

517
00:37:48,881 --> 00:37:50,361
Order whatever you want today.

518
00:37:50,361 --> 00:37:51,512
We have new dishes now.

519
00:37:52,056 --> 00:37:54,881
My apprentice said he'll treat us
to a feast once the case is closed.

520
00:37:54,881 --> 00:37:56,281
Yeah, my treat.

521
00:37:56,281 --> 00:37:57,200
Jiao places your order.

522
00:37:57,200 --> 00:37:58,321
I'll go cook for you.

523
00:37:58,761 --> 00:37:59,640
New dish, huh?

524
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:05,441
Is your plan going to work?

525
00:38:05,881 --> 00:38:09,560
What if that guy just stays at home?

526
00:38:10,001 --> 00:38:10,801
He can't wait.

527
00:38:11,600 --> 00:38:12,401
How so?

528
00:38:13,680 --> 00:38:14,680
I checked his account.

529
00:38:15,640 --> 00:38:18,080
He just tipped over 10,000
on a livestream platform.

530
00:38:18,441 --> 00:38:20,040
His balance is down
to pocket change now.

531
00:38:20,680 --> 00:38:22,560
If he doesn't figure out a way
to make money,

532
00:38:22,680 --> 00:38:24,001
he'll soon be going hungry.

533
00:38:31,881 --> 00:38:34,441
I did send a text message to Tian.

534
00:38:35,401 --> 00:38:37,600
His mom left his phone number
with us before.

535
00:38:38,281 --> 00:38:40,080
Such a big thing happened that day.

536
00:38:40,080 --> 00:38:41,441
How could I not tell him?

537
00:38:42,520 --> 00:38:45,520
It's just that at the time,
my mind was such a mess.

538
00:38:45,921 --> 00:38:47,560
So I didn't get a chance to tell you.

539
00:38:49,080 --> 00:38:52,200
Did it cause any problems for your work?

540
00:38:54,281 --> 00:38:55,200
No, not really.

541
00:38:56,001 --> 00:38:57,281
We're just here to confirm

542
00:38:57,281 --> 00:38:59,160
if the message came from you.

543
00:39:01,441 --> 00:39:03,001
Do you know Geng Tianchou well?

544
00:39:04,680 --> 00:39:05,680
Not really.

545
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:08,120
I just met him a very long time ago.

546
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:13,281
You and Jiang Yuzhen
weren't just old neighbors,

547
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:15,560
but classmates at primary school?

548
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:21,560
Why didn't you tell us this before?

549
00:39:23,801 --> 00:39:25,080
I didn't mind,

550
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:27,881
but Jiang cares about pride.

551
00:39:29,001 --> 00:39:30,761
She's proud.

552
00:39:31,160 --> 00:39:32,961
She didn't want others
to know about that.

553
00:39:33,520 --> 00:39:34,961
Even Liao didn't know.

554
00:39:36,240 --> 00:39:38,560
So tell us everything
you haven't said yet.

555
00:39:43,080 --> 00:39:45,841
You mean the car accident
a few years back?

556
00:39:48,080 --> 00:39:49,200
At the time,

557
00:39:49,200 --> 00:39:50,961
I truly didn't agree
with Liao's actions.

558
00:39:51,160 --> 00:39:52,600
I didn't support him,

559
00:39:53,080 --> 00:39:55,761
but the company was
at a critical moment in fundraising.

560
00:39:55,921 --> 00:39:57,200
So I didn't intervene.

561
00:39:58,120 --> 00:39:59,841
It's just that they were so pitiful.

562
00:40:00,481 --> 00:40:01,680
So I told Liao

563
00:40:02,680 --> 00:40:05,080
to give them more money in compensation.

564
00:40:06,401 --> 00:40:08,560
Do you think money can solve everything?

565
00:40:09,040 --> 00:40:10,240
Of course not.

566
00:40:11,481 --> 00:40:13,080
But the thing had already happened.

567
00:40:13,801 --> 00:40:15,881
Monetary compensation is better
than nothing, right?

568
00:40:18,321 --> 00:40:19,640
Did Jiang Yuzhen know?

569
00:40:20,680 --> 00:40:21,481
Yes.

570
00:40:22,001 --> 00:40:25,080
Did she also know
Liao found someone to take the fall?

571
00:40:26,441 --> 00:40:27,240
Yes.

572
00:40:28,200 --> 00:40:30,841
Then, did she know Zhao Junxin?

573
00:40:34,881 --> 00:40:36,281
She probably did.

574
00:40:36,921 --> 00:40:38,761
In that very neighborhood,

575
00:40:39,128 --> 00:40:40,640
Zhao Junxin put up a protest banner.

576
00:40:40,640 --> 00:40:42,481
It was Xiao Jiang
who saw it and told me.

577
00:40:45,281 --> 00:40:46,281
So, do you think

578
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:52,040
it's possible that Jiang Yuzhen
and Zhao Junxin knew each other before?

579
00:40:55,441 --> 00:40:58,361
Xiao Jiang and Zhao Junxin...

580
00:40:59,520 --> 00:41:01,361
Jiang Yuzhen had cancer.

581
00:41:01,361 --> 00:41:02,200
Terminal.

582
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:06,881
She bought herself
high-value life insurance.

583
00:41:10,560 --> 00:41:11,160
Well...

584
00:41:26,040 --> 00:41:27,401
Do you still send SMS messages?

585
00:41:28,921 --> 00:41:30,401
Now, people use WeChat.

586
00:41:31,441 --> 00:41:32,801
What if you're not WeChat friends?

587
00:41:33,921 --> 00:41:35,481
Then I'll make a call directly.

588
00:41:37,321 --> 00:41:39,801
Master, I also think

589
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:44,560
it's not quite normal
that Miao Xiaolan texted Geng Tianchou.

590
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:48,240
What I'm thinking now is,

591
00:41:48,841 --> 00:41:51,801
could there be another person?

592
00:41:54,281 --> 00:41:55,160
Miao Xiaolan?

593
00:41:55,761 --> 00:41:56,921
It's hard to say right now.

594
00:41:58,441 --> 00:42:01,881
Miao Xiaolan was previously excluded
since she had no means to carry it out.

595
00:42:02,720 --> 00:42:04,240
But considering the motive,

596
00:42:05,680 --> 00:42:08,240
she never mentioned the theft at all.

597
00:42:09,040 --> 00:42:10,680
If it's not that she doesn't care,

598
00:42:12,481 --> 00:42:13,401
it must be

599
00:42:14,441 --> 00:42:17,640
that she likely knew from the start
that Jiang Yuzhen took the stuff,

600
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:19,672
and that she even tacitly allowed it.

601
00:42:21,001 --> 00:42:22,841
Look into Miao Xiaolan again.

602
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:25,520
Release Geng Tianchou for now.

603
00:42:29,289 --> 00:42:32,782
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

604
00:42:36,576 --> 00:42:41,897
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

605
00:42:43,970 --> 00:42:48,824
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

606
00:42:49,630 --> 00:42:52,777
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

607
00:42:52,777 --> 00:42:55,881
♪To shield us from the storm♪

608
00:42:58,537 --> 00:43:03,671
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

609
00:43:05,641 --> 00:43:11,273
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

610
00:43:13,033 --> 00:43:16,617
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

611
00:43:17,769 --> 00:43:25,209
♪Converging into your form♪

612
00:43:25,641 --> 00:43:28,319
♪Looking up♪

613
00:43:28,319 --> 00:43:31,858
♪Such dazzling glory♪

614
00:43:32,841 --> 00:43:35,401
♪Like hope♪

615
00:43:35,401 --> 00:43:39,334
♪Reaching out its arms♪

616
00:43:40,201 --> 00:43:42,853
♪Cloaked in light♪

617
00:43:42,853 --> 00:43:47,337
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

618
00:43:47,337 --> 00:43:50,153
♪Traversing♪

619
00:43:50,153 --> 00:43:56,664
♪The battlefield of fate♪
